    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-18T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="413"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d413">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.6362/8–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-18T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 18, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1105. Urtel 1737 Aug 2<note n="90" xml:id="d413fn90">Not printed.</note> and 1809
                    Aug 9. Dept has been able to obtain removal of embargo on coal shipments to
                    Argentina and it is possible to ship 20,000 tons per month through Dec.</p>
                <p>Rather than start shipments gratuitously the Dept wishes to inform you that
                    shipments can be arranged and will be started when you advise the Dept that it
                    is desirable to do so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
